  "prompt": "Why did President Obama wait so long to show a birth certificate?",
  "response": "The issue of President Obama's birth certificate became a topic of public debate and controversy during his presidency, primarily fueled by conspiracy theories suggesting that he was not born in the United States. Obama initially addressed the issue in 2008 by releasing a certification of live birth, which is a legal document indicating that he was born in Hawaii. \n\nHowever, some critics continued to demand to see his long-form birth certificate. In 2011, in response to the persistent rumors and political pressure, Obama released the long-form version of his birth certificate, which confirmed that he was indeed born in Hawaii. \n\nObama and his administration suggested that they were focused on more pressing issues, such as the economy and healthcare, rather than engaging with the conspiracy theories. The decision to wait was likely influenced by a combination of factors, including the assessment of the legitimacy of the claims and the desire to not give undue attention to falsehoods.",
